      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "Translations along parallel lines produce congruent images.",
          "Translations along rays with a common endpoint produce similar images.",
          "A translation function represented as <math><msub><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>â€²</mo></math> takes as its input the location of a point <math><mi>P</mi></math> and translates it a distance <math><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math> in the direction <math><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math>.",
          "Isometries preserve shape and size, creating congruent figures.",
          "Dilations preserve shape only, creating similar figures."
        ]
      }
